THE deadly Coronavirus has been a menace to society. The sporting world has been impacted as much as everything else with major sporting events around the world suspended until further notice. This has left sports fanatics around the world twiddling their thumbs with no action to look forward to. The athletes themselves have also been left with more time on their hands than they perhaps know what to do with it. But the bigger picture remains – the good health of everyone across the world takes high priority. And famous sports people have made it their duty to raise awareness about the deadly virus to help stop the spread. They have been sharing messages of awareness, support and encouragement on social media. Below are messages from Cape Town City duo Thami Mkhize and Peter Leeuwenburgh   